  "chapter": {
    "number": 25,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Praise to the Victorious God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD, You are my God!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "I will exalt You;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will praise Your name.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For You have worked wonders—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "plans formed long ago—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in perfect faithfulness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, You have made the city a heap of rubble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fortified town a ruin.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The fortress of strangers is a city no more;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will never be rebuilt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, a strong people will honor You.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "The cities of ruthless nations will revere You.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For You have been a refuge for the poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a stronghold for the needy in distress,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a refuge from the storm,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a shade from the heat.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the breath of the ruthless",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is like rain against a wall,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "like heat in a dry land.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You subdue the uproar of foreigners.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "As the shade of a cloud cools the heat,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the song of the ruthless is silenced.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On this mountain the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will prepare a banquet for all the peoples,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a feast of aged wine, of choice meat,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of finely aged wine.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On this mountain He will swallow up",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the shroud that enfolds all peoples,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the sheet that covers all nations;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will swallow up death forever.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2597
          },
          {
            "text": "The Lord GOD will wipe away the tears from every face",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2598
          },
          {
            "text": "and remove the disgrace of His people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the whole earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "For the LORD has spoken."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And in that day it will be said, “Surely this is our God;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we have waited for Him, and He has saved us.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "This is the LORD for whom we have waited.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let us rejoice and be glad in His salvation.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the hand of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will rest on this mountain.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But Moab will be trampled in his place",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as straw is trodden into the dung pile.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will spread out his hands within it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as a swimmer spreads his arms to swim.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "His pride will be brought low,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "despite",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2599
          },
          {
            "text": "the skill of his hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The high-walled fortress will be brought down,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "cast to the ground, into the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
